data.title: National Currency, 5 Francs, Algeria
data.meta_description: National Currency, 5 Francs, Algeria.Banque de l'Algerie issue. The Banque de l'Algerie was founded in 1851 and was the note issuing authority thereafter. The bank issued notes under French Colonial, Vichy and Allied control.Note is creased and worn. Part of the bottom left corner is missing.

We have over a million object records online, and we are adding to this all the time. Our records are never finished.
